CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 28, 1950, pg. 3, reads: "Football Stars - These four football stars of Schenley High School's team are being honored at the Teen-Age [il.] at Godfrey's Skating Rink this Saturday. Left to right, Henry (Hank) Ford quarterback; Charlie (Mule) Hill, halfback; Donald (Muha) Miller, left tackle, and James [il.] Robinson, right end. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Schenley High School football players Henry "Hank" Ford, Charlie "Mule" Hill, Donald Miller, and James Robinson, posed in front of striped background, in Harris Studio
